<br>
What turned from a patch addition, Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday, is now stopped in its' tracks. Let us find out why. <br>
<br>
From Sanya: <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I didn't think people needed or wanted the gory details, but the patch isn't quite done because our producer just went home with the flu, and a number of other people are still recovering (albeit doing their recovering here in the office). Sorry. We're still going to put up a patch addition tomorrow by the close of business, but we cannot help the delay.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
* Cough *bullshit* Cough *<br>
<br>
From Mark Jacobs: <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We are charing $12.95 a month because we need to give the customer service that all of you should receive. These additional funds will help support our technical and customer support areas <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
After the first 3 months. <br>
<br>
Average Response time (Appeals): 5 hours, 12 minutes. <br>
Total Active Appeal Tickets in the queue (Noon, 1/09/02): 438 <br>
<br>
This spans 17 servers. An average appeal per server = 25.<br>
<br>
25 petitions per que takes 5 hours. When I was a guide, we would have 60-80 petitions and they would keep rolling in, and would have the que clear within 2 hours. You pay $9.89.  <br>
<br>
Mind you this was after the first three months. When before people were paying their $12.95 for this &quot;Premium&quot; customer service and getting reply times of 5 - 7 days.  <br>
<br>
Another carrot for the masses - while they notice that subscriptions are about to run out and are trying to get people to pay for one more month. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We have another Pendragon addition ALMOST finished... but not enough. Tomorrow is our hope for more goodies and details. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The so-called shapeshifting they implemented turns a zerker class into what is called a &quot;Vendo&quot; basically an average walking bear. With no additions except for the hero class it will give them a boost of 50% hit points. ? Makes perfect sense /rolls eyes.  For be it to them to actually make them turn into something original, they must use current models because they do not know how to program anything else into it. <br>
<br>
And of course while people beg for classes to be fixed and content to be added, they are busy doing the following. <br>
<br>
- Some of Bri Lieth's denizens were itemized (level 10-20). <br>
- The Cap of Mind Bending can now be dyed. <br>
- Mantle of bear-like visage can now be dyed. <br>
- The Singed Fellwood Shield had the class restrictions removed. Now only classes that can use large shields can equip it. It now raises Strength and Constitution instead of Piety. <br>
- The Jewel Dusted Robe now raises the Mentalism skill instead of Mind. <br>
- The Ancient Oak Longbow now raises the Longbow skill instead of bow. <br>
- The Glowing Sherrie beads is now set with its correct level. <br>
- The Rangers Charm should have its correct level now. <br>
- The Encrusted Truesilver necklace should have its correct level now. <br>
- The Eir Blessed Tunic now can take enamel dyes. <br>
- The Reincarnated Femur War Maul now has a 2 handed hammer graphic. <br>
- The Ebony Axe of Mindless Rage now raises Strength instead of Berserk. <br>
- The Gauntlets of Black Death now raises Strength instead of Celtic Dual Wield. <br>
- Winter's Spears now &quot;proc&quot; for appropriate level Hunters. <br>
- The &quot;Spirit Threaded Cloak&quot; (cabalist quest reward) now take emblems. <br>
- The Riva hauberk (Midgard) can be dyed.<br>
<br>
I am glad I can now dye those items which will be useless in 5 levels. Thanks Mythic <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Glad to see you are working hard on your game and actually have a clue. <br>
<br>
Everything the high level players in your game wanted. To be able to dye armor on their twinks. <br>
